@@ -389,0 +389,8 @@
+  // Return the precise offset of load/store instruction for null check.
+  // On aarch64, no matter what addressing mode is used, LDR/STR is always the last
+  // instruction in the instruction clause emitted for a load/store machine node. So
+  // it will return the beginning offset of latest instruction,
+  // i.e. (the end offset of latest instruction - sizeof(one unit of instruction)).
+  // Other platforms will directly return "previous_offset".
+  static int offset_for_null_check(int previous_offset, int last_insn_offset);
+
